42
0:02:07.28,000 --> 0:02:08,000
You felt upset.

43
0:02:08.287,000 --> 0:02:09,000
You just wanted to dive in.

44
0:02:10.541,000 --> 0:02:11,000
By the 10th time,

45
0:02:12.165,000 --> 0:02:14,000
you started to become less upset

46
0:02:14.641,000 --> 0:02:17,000
and you just started peeling the label off.

47
0:02:18.071,000 --> 0:02:2,000
By the 100th time, at least for me,

48
0:02:20.48,000 --> 0:02:21,000
I became numb to it.

49
0:02:22.212,000 --> 0:02:24,000
I simply picked up the piece of fruit,

50
0:02:25.103,000 --> 0:02:29,000
dug at it with my nails, tried to flick it off,

51
0:02:29.215,000 --> 0:02:3,000
and then wondered,

52
0:02:30.771,000 --> 0:02:33,000
"Was there another sticker?"

53
0:02:35.68,000 --> 0:02:36,000
So why is that?

54
0:02:36.974,000 --> 0:02:38,000
Why do we get used to everyday things?

55
0:02:39.126,000 --> 0:02:42,000
Well as human beings, we have limited brain power.

56
0:02:42.274,000 --> 0:02:46,000
And so our brains encode the everyday things we do into habits

57
0:02:47.043,000 --> 0:02:5,000
so we can free up space to learn new things.

58
0:02:50.62,000 --> 0:02:52,000
It's a process called habituation

59
0:02:52.662,000 --> 0:02:55,000
and it's one of the most basic ways, as humans, we learn.

60
0:02:57.596,000 --> 0:02:59,000
Now, habituation isn't always bad.

61
0:03:00.975,000 --> 0:03:01,000
